canonical:
  title: 親享宗廟賀牋
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 肇建丕基克惇尊敬之儀明禋淸廟用致著存之誠喜溢朝郊慶緜宗社恭惟溫恭允塞寬裕有容啓迪後人齊天造之草昧達觀新邑欣寢成之孔安禮備冬烝樂諧夏奏伏念職叨奉鉞跡阻趨班想宣室之受釐效華封之祝壽
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 親享宗廟賀牋
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 肇建丕基。克惇尊敬之儀。明禋淸廟。用致著存之誠。喜溢朝郊。慶緜宗社。恭惟溫恭允塞。寬裕有容。啓迪後人。齊天造之草昧。達觀新邑。欣寢成之孔安。禮備冬烝。樂諧夏奏。伏念職叨奉鉞。跡阻趨班。想宣室之受釐。效華封之祝壽。
korean:
  title: 친향 종묘 하 전
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 큰 터를 비로소 세워 조종(祖宗)을 존경하는 의식을 돈독히 하시고, 청묘(淸廟)에 깨끗하게 제사를 올려 신령(神靈)이 나타나 계시는 치성(致誠)을 드리오니, 기쁨이 조야(朝野)에 넘치고 경사가 종사(宗社)에 가득하도소이다. 공손히 생각하옵건대, 온공(溫恭)하시고 진실로 깊으시며 관유(寬裕)하고 포용성이 계셔, 후인(後人)을 가르쳐 인도하여 하늘이 만드신 초매(草昧 개화되기 전의 세상)를 가지런히 하시고, 새 도읍을 두루 관찰하시어 침묘(寢廟)가 편안히 이뤄짐을 기뻐하오니, 예(禮)는 겨울의 증제(烝祭)를 갖추고, 악(樂)은 하(夏)의 주악(奏樂)에 맞도소이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 외람되게 병직(兵職)을 맡사와 반열(班列)에 추창하지 못하옵고, 선실(宣室)의 음복주 받으심을 상상하면서 화봉인(華封人)의 축수(祝壽)를 본뜨옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0510&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Congratulatory Memorial on the Royal Sacrifice at the Ancestral Temple
  author: Lee Chaem
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The great foundation newly established honors the solemn rituals of reverence for ancestors. Pure offerings ascend to the luminous temple, and sincere devotion draws forth the manifest presence of the divine spirits. Joy overflows through court and countryside, blessings abound for the royal house and ancestral shrines.

    I humbly reflect upon Your Majesty's gentle sincerity and profound truthfulness, your boundless magnanimity and capacious grace. You guide and enlighten those who come after, ordering the primordial chaos as heaven itself ordains, and surveying the new capital with delight that its shrines stand secure and serene. The rites are complete with winter's solemn sacrifice, the music harmonizes with summer's sacred melodies.

    Though I humbly serve in the military ranks, I remain distant from the procession of officials. Yet I dare imagine receiving the blessings granted in the Hall of Heaven's Assembly, and humbly pattern my wishes after the sage's prayer for ten thousand years of life.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Hall of Heaven's Assembly' (宣室) references an ancient tradition of imperial audiences where divine blessings were conferred.
    - The reference to the sage's prayer echoes the Zhuangzi's account of the old man of Huafeng, whose blessings comprised longevity, honor, longevity again, and a peaceful death—the classical expression of complete human fulfillment.
